litics in operation within the relationships of these international couples. Overall, the book discusses how ethnic identity intersects with gender in the negotiation of spaces and power relations between and amongst couples; and the role states and structural inequalities play in these processes, resulting in a reconfiguration of our notions of what international marriages are and how powerful gender and the state are in understanding the power relations in these unions.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aForeign spouseszJapan. 0aIntercountry marriagezJapan. 0aInterracial coupleszJapan. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  ajapan, japanese, japanese american, immigrant, japanese immigrant, hawaii, california, ancestry, diaspora, global diaspora, industrial, migrant, migrant experience, heritage, mixed heritage, tradition, marriage, marriage migrants, international couples, international marriages, bicultural children, marriage politics, Asian studies.1 aBalgoa, Nelia G., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBerta, Péter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYamamoto, Beverley Anne, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021 Englishz978311075418608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology 2021z9783110753967oZDB-23-DSL08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076647940uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9781978809055?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/97